text: car-sharing companies Zipcar had a warm
reception for its IPO today with the
shares rising sixty-seven percent at the
open the company raised more than one
hundred seventy four million dollars and
it's offering about 31 percent more than
it expected analysts said the strong
investor interest in Zipcar is due to
the company's leading position in a new
market users who the company dubs zip
stirs sign up for an annual membership
which allows them to use the cars by the
hour or by the day gas a parking spot
and insurance are included we had this
mission years ago to really look at
cities in a different way and really
have a very different point of view
about transportation and cities and and
we're really getting it done now we have
five hundred and sixty thousand zip
stirs out there they believe in what we
see that the world in cities of
transportation is changing now but the
company is capital intensive with more
than a thousand cars in its inventory it
has raised more than 50 million dollars
from private investors before its IPO
and Zipcar is yet to turn a profit it
has accumulated losses of more than 65
million and says it plans to lose money
this year meanwhile competitors are
trying to catch up a similar program run
by the rental car company Hertz is
available in eight markets compared to
zip cars availability in more than 200
this is Evelyn wristlet for deal book at
the New York Times
